5:
So you've been to the same worlds
we've been to, Dia?
8:
Yup! After returning all of the bugged
memories, I decided to go on a journey
of my own!
12:
By yourself? I'm surprised that traitor
didn't have anything to say about it.
15:
Well, Regis insisted on coming along... 
so I just slipped away without telling
him!
17:
This was something I wanted to do on
my own from the start anyway.
28:
The first world I visited was just a
wasteland as far as the eye could see.
31:
But I eventually found a feline girl
teasing a canid boy.
33:
They showed me their village, and there 
were all sorts of furry friends there!
40:
Yep! It seems they just started building 
the place too. One thing's for sure—
those cats and dogs could SING!
47:
After that, I went to a world that was
pretty much all water! I'd never traveled
by boat before!
49:
I met some mermaids there, and we
had a contest to see who could lure
more pirates with our singing!
51:
It ended up in a tie, I think. Those pirates
never knew what hit 'em!
56:
We dabbled in a bit of piracy of our own,
didn't we?
64:
For real?! Wow, I totally wish I could've
had a chance!
69:
I've had enough piracy for a lifetime,
thanks.
73:
After that, I found myself in a world full
of sand! It was kinda scary at first.
75:
But then I met some children who were
super nice to me. They gave me a cloak
to hide from the scary grown-ups!
79:
Oh, and there were these gorgeous
dancers! When they performed with me
in the moonlight, it was so beautiful...
83: That's not the impression I got.
95:
Anyway, after that was a forest world,
full of verdant life!
97:
There was an old guy there... I think he
was dead? But still living... sort of.
What's the deal with that?
101: Ah, wise Regitare. A sage among sages.
104:
He called himself the king of the dead
or something at first. It totally spooked
me out!
107:
But he turned out to be a total
sweetheart! He even prepared a stage
for me to perform in the forest!
109:
I'd never seen a place so green before.
And when I began to sing, all these
mushrooms came out of nowhere!
113:
They must have been Shroombo's
relatives.
116:
Yeah, there were red, blue, green, pink,
and yellow mushrooms—an entire
spectrum!
121:
I would love to see you perform 
onstage sometime, Dia.
130:
Now that's an idea—a performance to
celebrate your arrival in Starview
Village!
133:
Let's start the show! Activating sound
unit. Deploying audio field!
138:
All eyes and electrons on me!
Here. We. Goooooo!
